Extruded snacks hold a significant market share globally, with various segments offering options to cater to different consumer preferences. When segmented by type, extruded snacks are classified into potato-based, corn-based, rice-based, mixed grains, and others. Potato-based extruded snacks are popular for their crispy texture and range of flavors. Corn-based options often include shapes like rings or twists and appeal to consumers looking for a crunchy snack. Rice-based extruded snacks offer a lighter alternative, suitable for those seeking gluten-free options or a distinct taste. Mixed grains combine different grains like wheat, oats, or barley to offer a healthier snacking choice.

Distribution channels play a crucial role in the extruded snacks market. Supermarkets and hypermarkets are primary retail channels for extruded snacks due to their wide reach and ability to offer a variety of brands and flavors in one place. Convenience stores also contribute significantly to the market, providing consumers with quick and easy access to extruded snacks. The rise of online retail has further expanded the reach of extruded snacks, allowing consumers to purchase their favorite snacks from the comfort of their homes.

